1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
This video demonstrates how MetricMind integrates with LinkedIn to analyze digital presence signals and publish insights.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
MetricMind is a digital intelligence platform that detects early signals across websites and social platforms.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Users begin by accessing the MetricMind platform and signing in.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Users can authenticate using Google Sign-In or by entering their MetricMind account credentials.

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:40,000
After logging in, the user enters a website of their choice to analyze digital presence signals.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:48,000
MetricMind scans the website to detect publicly observable signals related to digital presence.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
These signals may include website structure, social links, and indicators of digital visibility.

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:04,000
This initial analysis provides the foundation for generating intelligence insights.

9
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:12,000
After the analysis, the user connects their LinkedIn account from within the MetricMind platform.

10
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:20,000
MetricMind uses the official LinkedIn OAuth 2.0 authorization flow to request permission from the user.

11
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:28,000
After authorization, MetricMind retrieves basic profile information such as name and email.

12
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:36,000
This confirms the LinkedIn identity connection and activates the MetricMind LinkedIn integration.

13
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:44,000
MetricMind allows users to share intelligence insights directly to LinkedIn.

14
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Here the user initiates the publishing flow from within the MetricMind platform.

15
00:01:52,000 --> 00:02:00,000
MetricMind prepares an insight generated from the website analysis.

16
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:08,000
The LinkedIn post composer opens, allowing the user to review the content before publishing.

17
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:16,000
The user can edit the message, confirm the audience, and publish the insight.

18
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Once published, the post appears on the user's LinkedIn feed.

19
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Other LinkedIn members can interact with the post through reactions and comments.

20
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:40,000
MetricMind analyzes these engagement signals to understand how insights spread across professional networks.

21
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:48,000
MetricMind is designed to support organizations that manage LinkedIn pages.

22
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Page administrators can publish insights and monitor engagement signals from their organization.

23
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:04,000
MetricMind also tracks post performance indicators such as reactions, comments, and visibility signals.

24
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:12,000
These capabilities enable community managers to better understand engagement and digital visibility.

25
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:20,000
This concludes the demonstration of the MetricMind LinkedIn integration and its community management use cases.


